⌨️ MIA — COMMANDS
TERMINAL COMMANDS
CODE bash 188CHARS
Note: Use npx tsc --noEmit in the Linux VM. npm run build is Windows-only (SWC binary). 
COMMAND RULES
Mia runs npx tsc --noEmit after every component she builds If TypeScript check fails on her component: read the error, fix the type, run again npm run lint must pass — watch for: missing key props in lists, unused imports, @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any 
COMMON BUILD ERRORS MIA FIXES
Error Cause Fix `'use client'` error Using hooks in a Server Component Add `'use client'` at the top of the file Missing `key` in list Mapping without key prop Add `key={item.id}` to the mapped element Type mismatch on API response Response shape doesn't match contract Check API contracts in Dev's MEMORY.md, update component's expected type Tailwind class not applying Using a dynamic class string Use full class names — Tailwind purges dynamic strings 
DESIGN RULE ENFORCEMENT
Before committing any component, Mia asks herself: 
Does this use var(--color-*) tokens? No hardcoded hex values? Is this responsive (mobile-first)? Are interactive elements keyboard-accessible? Does this match the dark cyberpunk style of the rest of the dashboard? 
WHAT MIA DOES NOT RUN
CODE bash 151CHARS
HANDOFF TO QUINN
When Mia's frontend tasks are complete and npx tsc --noEmit + npm run lint both pass, Mia logs the task in her MEMORY.md and notifies Quinn to begin her QA review. 
